705943f-a.title: Brooklyn: Neptune Avenue - 28th Street (West)
705943f-a.text:
Neptune Ave., north side, east of West 28th Street, showing a former ex cursion barge, which served as a place of sale for rowboats. It does not appear in the 1929 Brooklyn Atlas. Also seen is Gravesend Bay.
June 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

702692f-a.title: Brooklyn: 28th Street (West) - Neptune Avenue
702692f-a.text:
West 28th Street, north from Neptune Avenue toward Gravesend Bay, showing a W. P. A. sewer project.
1936
Works Progress Administration
Five Boroughs Project
